      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Force and displacement residuals monitored; convergence tolerance set to 0.5% force norm.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear quasi-static solution uses Newton-Raphson iteration with force-norm convergence criterion of 0.5%. All load steps converged within 12 iterations; no divergence or cutback events recorded across the 11-construct ensemble."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent analyst review of model setup; documented simulation workflow with checklist.",
      "rationale": "A second analyst independently reviewed boundary conditions, material assignments, and contact definitions against the simulation plan. Discrepancies identified in initial contact stiffness settings were corrected prior to production runs. Use-error checklist archived."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification provided for continuum elasto-plastic constitutive model and frictional contact formulation relative to COU physics.",
      "rationale": "Titanium alloy screw and rod modeled with bilinear isotropic hardening calibrated to tensile coupon data. Polyacetal vertebral body blocks modeled with elastic-perfectly-plastic law. Frictional contact (mu = 0.3) applied at all interfaces based on literature. Model form is appropriate for quasi-static monotonic loading in the COU."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric inputs traceable to measurements; input uncertainty characterised via Monte Carlo sampling across material property distributions.",
      "rationale": "Titanium alloy elastic modulus and yield stress drawn from lot-specific tensile coupon measurements (n=6 coupons). Polyacetal block properties from supplier datasheet supplemented by in-house compression tests. Geometric dimensions from CMM measurements of production screws. Input uncertainty characterised via 1000-sample Monte Carlo propagation; a screening sensitivity study described in the UQ report identifies material yield stress and rod diameter as the highest-variance contributors, though the structured sensitivity analysis artifact has not been separately linked to this package."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 constructs from production lots; dimensional inspection records available.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled from production-representative hardware. Dimensional inspection (CMM) confirms all components within drawing tolerances. Constructs distributed across two independent laboratories to assess inter-laboratory variability."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Multiple loading rates or environmental conditions bracketing clinical use; at minimum two test configurations.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single quasi-static loading rate (5 mm/min) per ASTM F1717 protocol. Clinical loading encompasses a range of rates and postures not captured by a single condition. Achieved level 2 (single condition characterised) does not meet the required level 3 (multiple conditions). This gap is acknowledged and accepted given the standardised nature of the F1717 protocol and the conservative quasi-static assumption."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA inputs mapped directly to measured experimental parameters; traceability matrix documented.",
      "rationale": "A traceability matrix maps each FEA input (geometry, material, boundary condition) to the corresponding experimental measurement or specification. CMM measurements used to set nominal geometry in simulation; coupon-derived material properties used directly. No surrogate inputs required."
    },
