      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly map to clinical failure modes and regulatory submission endpoints.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and are directly relevant to clinical construct stability and fatigue life prediction. These QoIs are the same endpoints used in the 510(k) submission."
